The Hawks have arrested a 39-year-old suspect in connection with the murder of anti-gang unit investigator, Charl Kinnear. The suspect was arrested in Gauteng on Wednesday. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Hawks have confirmed an arrest in connection with the murder of gang investigator Charl Kinnear. The 39-year-old suspect was arrested in Gauteng on Wednesday. He will appear in the Bishop Lavis Magistrate's Court on Friday. READ:Â R1m reward for info leading to arrest of Kinnear killers Kinnear was assassinated outside his Cape Town home last week. He worked on several high-profile investigations at the Anti Gang Unit. The directorate says more arrests may follow as investigations continue.